            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After 20 min, cut the <strong>Cumberland sausages</strong> into rough bite-sized pieces </p>\n<p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Top, tail, peel and dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></span></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sausage pieces</strong> and cook for 3-5 min or until browned all over </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">While the sausage is cooking</span>, boil a kettle</p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Once the <strong>sausage pieces </strong>are browned, reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>carrot</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 4-6 min or until softened </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>Knorr chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Drain and rinse the<strong> cannellini beans</strong></span></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1835.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> onions</strong> and <strong>carrots </strong>have softened, increase the heat to medium-high and add the <strong>chicken stock</strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">, <strong>Marmite </strong>and <strong>cannellini beans</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Add<strong> half </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[all]</span> the<strong> chopped tomatoes </strong>and cook</span> 5-8 min or until reduced to the consistency of baked beans <span class=\"text-highlight\">- this is your <strong>sausage and bean stew </strong></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Transfer any remaining chopped tomatoes to a bowl, cover and keep in the fridge to use up to 3 days later</span></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
